This memorandum, signed by President Joseph R. Biden Jr., delegates authority to the Secretary of State to direct the drawdown of up to $300 million in defense articles and services from the Department of Defense, as well as military education and training, to provide assistance to Ukraine. The Secretary of State is also given the power to make the necessary determinations required under section 506(a)(1) of the Foreign Assistance Act of 1961. The memorandum further instructs the Secretary of State to publish this document in the Federal Register.